     <div type="encomium">
   <pb facs="16"/>
   <head>To my honour'd Friend vpon his Introduction.</head>
   <l>IF they which finde out cleere &amp; happy wayes</l>
   <l>To wealthy kingdomes, where the trea<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>sure payes</l>
   <l>Their cost agen,</l>
   <l>Deserue to haue their name</l>
   <l>Shine, in the list of fame,</l>
   <l>What honour then,</l>
   <l>Shall we and time bestow</l>
   <l>On him, to whom we owe,</l>
   <l>For this neere way to know?</l>
   <l>Grammar which opens to the arts, had lost</l>
   <l>Her golden key, this new one is thy cost;</l>
   <l>Ages were spent,</l>
   <l>And many Rockes our youth</l>
   <l>Were forc'd to clime to truth,</l>
   <l>Till this was lent.</l>
   <l>For which great trust, since we</l>
   <l>Are bad securitie,</l>
   <l>The Arts are bound to thee.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>Ia. Shirley.</signed>
   </closer>
